Fragment that contains a List that is populated using an ExecutorService.

1. Calling code that uses Executor Service to use Futures for storing result.
2. Polulate the ListView of the Fragment on receiving result from the Futures.

    public void displayMoviesByYear() {

        // Using ExecutorService to do the background connection
        MoviesExecutor mv = MoviesExecutor.getInstance();
        Future<List<Movie>> future = mv.getMoviesByYear(year);
        List<Movie> list = null;
        try {
            // Do something else first
            Thread.sleep(2000);
            list = future.get();
        } catch (ExecutionException e) {
            // Do something if exception is thrown
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            // Do something if exception is throws
        }
        if (list != null) {
            movies = list;
            arrayAdapter = new MoviesAdapter(getActivity(), R.layout.text_view, movies);
            myList.setAdapter(arrayAdapter);
        }

    }
